cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on task execution in cloud computing, which falls under the domain of distributed and parallel computing. 
2. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The proposed algorithm aims to reduce the cost and execution time of tasks, which is relevant to computational finance and science. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The communication framework between broker and virtual machine is a key aspect of the proposed work, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The proposed algorithm involves scheduling policies for virtual machines and cloudlets, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The implementation of the proposed algorithm in CloudSim involves software engineering principles and practices.
